    <thetext>In 8.6.2 &quot;Object Internal Properties and Methods&quot;,
you could add a couple things to the definition of &quot;SpecOp&quot;:

(1)
In addition to the given parameters, a procedure/operation that implements a SpecOp will also have access to an object, namely the object on which it is invoked.

(2)
Rather than returning a value of the given type, a &apos;SpecOp&apos; may return an abrupt completion.</thetext>
